title: For Sale/Trade:  WW2 Star 1911
postcontent: I am the second owner of this soviet captured  Star 1911 9mm made in 1943. The gun has custom “firewood” grips and comes with 1 magazine. It was manufactured in 1943 and certain parts of the firearm are stained red from the cosmolene that the first owner, a friend of mine, cleaned off. The finish isnt perfect it’s around 75% , it was blued at the star factory and then when the Soviets gave them over to dealers, the one mine came from was reblued before being sold to civilians. All stamps are still intact and look great! This is a great collectors item. Stars that can be bought today are generally from the 70-90s era so WW2 models are not nearly as common so that is why the pricing is different. This particular pistol has a story behind it due to a eagle holding a swatztika on the grip. The original dealer who had a crate of stars knew that some stars were sold to the nazis during the war. So he attempted to sell them as Nazi owned due to the selling price of originals being 3-4 times the price of a normal WW2 Star. The stamp can be seen in person but a camera can’t focus on it. The last picture, the Ñ, is the Spanish proofmark for 1943. Beside is is the verification stamp placed by the proofhouse. Star has an official website and they show all the dates for every proofmark ever stamped on a Star product. All numbers match.This is a great piece for Spanish collectors or just someone who wants a WW2 1911! If you have any questions just ask!
